coffees.name: Dutch Boy Blend
coffees.description: This is our signature, medium roast, consisting of Central American and African coffee beans. This coffee has notes including vanilla, chocolate, and almond. We believe it makes the perfect cup of drip, pour over and espresso coffees. Pair it with cream or drink it black, we are more than confident you will enjoy every ounce.

coffees.name: Single Origin Brazil
coffees.description: This single origin coffee, sourced from Brazil, has a medium body, mild acidity, and tasting notes of green apple and chocolate.

coffees.name: Single Origin Organic Papua New Guinea
coffees.description: This organic, single origin coffee, has a medium body and medium acidity. Tasting notes include dark chocolate, dried cherry and blueberry.

coffees.name: Single Origin Costa Rica Honey Process
coffees.description: This Costa Rican single origin has a medium body, a bright acidity, and tasting notes of Honey, Almond, and Bourbon.

coffees.name: Dutch Boy Dark
coffees.description: Our Signature Dutch Boy Blend roasted to a darker profile for a stronger, heavier taste.

coffees.name: Dutch Boy Blonde
coffees.description: Our signature blend of Central American and African coffees, but roasted to a lighter profile creating a bright and lighter flavor.

coffees.name: Single Origin Ethiopia Sidamo
coffees.description: This bold single origin, sourced from Ethiopia, grows in the region of Sidamo and includes tasting notes of Cane sugar and Plum.

coffees.name: Single Origin Nicaragua - Farm Direct - Honey Process
coffees.description: Tasting notes of blueberry, pomegranate, and citrus. This is a shop favorite, we love it paired with chocolate croissant or a bagel with cream cheese. The quality and freshness of this coffee is unmatched!

coffees.name: Single Origin Guatemala Huehuetenango SHB
coffees.description: This mild and smooth single origin, sourced from Guatemala, grows in the region of Huehuetenango and includes tasting notes of granny smith apples, raspberries, and cane sugar.
coffees.flavorNotes: Granny Smith Apple | Raspberries | Cane Sugar

coffees.name: Organic Colombia - Excelsio
coffees.description: This Organic Columbian coffee is from the Antioquia region of Columbia. Antioquia is in the Northwest portion of the country, lying mostly within the Andes mountains and reaching toward the Caribbean Sea. The excelsio grade of coffee is a smaller than an average bean but full of flavor and fantastic quality.
coffees.flavorNotes: Navel Orange | Red Grapes | Milk Chocolate | Caramel

coffees.name: Tanzania - Mbeya Region - Natural Process
coffees.description: Indulge in the rich and flavorful taste of our Tanzania Mbeya Region Natural Process coffee beans. Carefully sourced from the lush Mbeya region, these beans undergo a unique natural process that brings out their distinctive flavors. With every sip, you'll experience notes of fruity sweetness and a smooth, velvety finish. Elevate your coffee experience and savor the essence of Mbeya with our exceptional Tanzania Mbeya Region Natural Process coffee beans. We roast these beans to a light-medium profile that highlights the natural Strawberry and Citrus flavors.
